      <section eId="sec_18_2_50">
        <num>18-2-50</num>
        <content>
          <p>Within 30 days after filing the assignment, the assignee shall notify each creditor that the same has been filed. Within 30 days after the date the assignee is served with the complaint attacking the assignment, he shall give notice of the filing of the complaint to each creditor named. Depositing a letter in the post office, stamped and properly addressed, shall be sufficient notice under this Code section.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1894, p. 90, ยง 17; Civil Code 1895, ยง 2714; Civil Code 1910, ยง 3247; Code 1933, ยง 28-318.)</p>
